The holidays are a great time to help spread joy and love. And our Santa Cruz took some time to do just that this season. Take a look at some of the fun we had during a #CruzCares week! 

• Youth Holiday Shopping - 25 youth from School 21 in Paterson, NJ enjoyed holiday shopping alongside alumnus @victorcruz 

• Eva’s Village Winter Donation - with help from some of our amazing partners, we were able to donate $5,000 and over 100 coats and 150 pairs of socks to an organization with years of impactful work 

• Knicks at Night - @victorcruz invited students from Paterson, NJ’s new STEAM high school, who’ve shown tremendous academic progress since the start of the school year, to a suite game at MSG.

Special THANK YOU to our dear friends who help us keep smiles on faces: @BenjieWimberley @SarahSmiles531 @FootLockerNYC @KITH @TommyHilfiger @STAMPD @NYGiants @TheGarden

This week many students close their books to the 2022-2023 school year and prepare for summer plans. Here’s a look into the some of our own impact this academic year. 
•STEAM High School - Victor joined Paterson school and city officials at the ribbon cutting ceremony for the new STEAM High School, which now operates in his former high school building. 
•Victor visits during STEAM Day. Students at STEAM High School selects an academia pathways in either Engineering, Medical and Dental Arts, Sustainable Studies or Computer Science and Information Technology. 
•A group of students who have demonstrated academic progress attend a NY Knicks game.
•Juniors at STEAM High School participated in a 4 month long program of financial literacy led by our J.P. Morgan partners. 
•Students from Paterson were able to visit the  News12 station and learn directly from their anchors and production team.
